The paper deals with algorithmic solutions for parity games, which are a fundamental topic in computer science and logic. The paper's focus on 3-color parity games, which can be solved in polynomial time, suggests that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's use of attractor constructions and its analysis of running times suggest that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The paper's application of parity games to express safety and liveness properties suggests that it may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
